It's the most selfless job in the world.

She works 24/7, unpaid and overtime and even faces criticism from us sometimes and still she puts in the effort every single day to shower us with love and affection. Mother's Day should not be just one day per year, but every moment of our lives.

@geezywing @literallydevice @edwinrawrrr

My mum called Mother-in-Law, Susheela  is my Power Mom  who made me laugh.... wiped my tears....hugged me tight....cheered me on... going strong....drove me little crazy at times.... A mother for 9 child a grand Mother for 14 grand children, sacrificed her life as a full time home maker taking care of the family needs and cooking healthy delicious food 365 days all round the clock, from breakfast to suppers. Besides she is a Carnatic Singer who in her little leisure time volunteers to teach music to the children who cannot afford and and performs in Temples and bring back her childhood hobby to life in her late 70’s. Further age never stopped her hobby of growing a nursery at the backyards of the house, plenty of organic fruits, vegetables and flowers. She always insists and inspire others that age is not a barrier if we are determined in achieving our goals. She always explains us that Love is the only gift that one generation can pass on to the others and always family come first and make our life happiest within our means,  keep smiling to vibrate  an healthy environment. Life is a journey and there will be rainbows in our way to shade our cloudy days. She is indeed a Super woman who has surpassed several tsunamis of life with. Every minute of my life spent with you is amazing and meaningful. Mom, You are indeed a Super Mom with simple living and high thinking in nature with generosity, graciousness and magnanimity. A salute to my Super Mom from the bottom of my heart. 
